article.headline: Boise State 98, UTEP 94
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) --Jermaine Blackburn scored 18 of his 25 points in the second half as Boise State came back to beat Texas-El Paso 98-94 Saturday night. Boise State (9-2, 1-0 WAC) trailed 81-75 with 6:43 left before Blackburn led the Broncos' rally, scoring eight points in a 23-13 run to close the game. UTEP (9-2, 0-1) pulled to within 90-89 with 1:17 left when Chris Craig was fouled while shooting a 3-pointer and completed the four-point play. But Boise State held on as Eric Lane and Booker Nabors each hit free throws to put the game away. Lane and Aaron Hayes added 17 points each for Boise State. Jason Ellis led the Broncos with nine rebounds. Omar Thomas led UTEP with 29 points, going 8-of-12 from the field and 13-of-13 from the free throw line. John Tofi added 21 points and Craig had 13. Boise State led 21-8 to start the game, but UTEP rallied and trailed 47-46 at halftime.
